om say, wearing 10 6ac 65hp rings)<br><br>I'd like to see tink bags drop at least .5 stone.<br><br>I'd like Tkick to NEVER land for less than what a regular flying kick could.<br><br>I *really* want to see a Plane of Tranquility for us Quellious monks.<br><br>I would love to be able to choose from a few different styles of fighting. It might work something like this:<br><br>Guard/Recon - We wouldnt be able to melee and could only use ranged weapons. Aggro radius is considerably smaller. Damage taken when hit would be significantly lower than normal.<br><br>Defensive fighting - You hit your opponent for less, but take less damage when you do get hit.<br><br>Traditional - The way we hit and take damage currently.<br><br>Aggressive fighting - Our damage output would be considerably raised, but the damage taken when hit would increase as well.<br><br>Rage - Damage output is raised A LOT, but we take an enormous amount of damage if we get hit and we risk drawing aggro much more than normal. Our aggro radius is raised considerably. A couple riposts or an add that hits us first could kill us instantly, but it would be worth the risk in many situations.<br><br>You could only change your mode of fighting each 30 minutes. This would keep people from exploiting the fighting styles. I'm thinking 6aa points each for aggressive and defensive. Both would be available. 6aa points for Guard/Recon OR Rage - you couldnt have both, but you COULD give one up, spend three more AA points, and get the other if you choose to.<br><br>In addition, you couldnt go from Tradtional to Rage, or from Rage to Defensive. You could only move one step per 30 minutes. Kind of likie letting the anger build up in you before you can become a killing machine, and slowly cooling off to get back to normal fighting.<br><br> <p>[Cexios Sharevari] <BR>[55 monk of Xev] <br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=240571">My Junk</A</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778