 a quest, they should be rewarded.  Why not reward well for, say, a hundred rare drops off of a fairly easy mob for one or two people to do?  Why not reward for someone taking the time to max all factions relating to not just one, but several gods?<br>Also, I think they should implement quests that would allow someone to change their deity!  I think there are quite a few people that would be interested in that.  I know that I'd consider changing over from agnosticism if the rewards were worth it.  I know my wife, for RP purposes, wants to change her deity (she plays a DE cleric following Innoruuk, but wants to follow Quellious or another &quot;good&quot; god).<br>One more idea I had...  Make a Plane of the Void.  Someplace that represents the Nameless from which all the gods sprung.  A place where, maybe, agnostics won't feel left out of the entire PoP expansion.<br>Okay, done whining for now.  I'll let ya know if I think of anything else.<br><br>Seth <p><IMG SRC=http://www3.telus.net/robbscrapola/Can%20sig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublytzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blytzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://blytzz.freewebspace.com/images/train.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 894<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/10/02 10:20:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29345.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://blytzz.freewebspace.com/images/train.gif/images/buddies/badassbuddy_com-train!.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP advancement, what do we want?</span><hr size=1> Being able to combo our special attacks similar to a fighting game would be the pwn <p>-The Everquest player formerly known as Blytzz-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td 