less it was made extremely valuable. Like crit mend 6 would have to make it 100% crits for me to even consider it. Point is, I like the idea for some skills but others it would be pointless.<br><br>As far as new things, I've always thought we should have gotten an H2H mastery skill. It should increase our H2H accuracy 2, 5 and 10%. In addition, i'd like to have a second ambidexterity type skill that makes us dual wield 100% of the time. Perhaps something to make us double attack 100% of the time would be nice too. I know I'd love to quad everytime ;0 That might be a bit much offense though, but generally I'd like to see our damage output supplemented via AA. <p><img src="http://www.stasisprexus.com/uploads/Axiss/sig.gif"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10004">Magelo Profile</a><a href="mailto:axissglox@hotmail.com">Contact Me</a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaehoon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taehoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 575<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/10/02 11:21:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29345.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP advancement, what do we want?</span><hr size=1> I think it's about time for a 15min refresh 100% mem wipe FD skill.<br><br>A skill to add Counter Attack to Riposte...would do the chain combo we've wanted.<br><br>I want an ability that ties a proc to Eagle Strike, the proc being a small hate reducer.<br><br>Endless Bandage.  If Rangers can get Endless Quiver, we can get Endless Bandage!<br><br>Tranquil Transcendence.  What this would do is send you to your bind point.  It's activated like camping.  Sit down, /tt, 30sec later you get sent to your bind point.  Next time you zone or sit and /tt again, you get sent back to where you started.  This would fit the roleplay sense that Monks can venture out into the wild and and be self sufficient, but yet use their meditative powers to shift their being to a place of rest and rejuvination.  Ideally this is useful for gathering supplies/money/items to trade.  It would be best to limit it so that you can't be buffed or healed while in your bind point phase.  Just a neat idea that would never be implemented, but would be nice to make Monks much more unique and to help us offset that weight penalty. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490" style="text-decoration: none" target=_blank><b>Taehoon</b></a> • <a href="http://www.monkly-business.com" style="text-decoration: none" target=_blank><b>Iksar Grandmaster</b></a> <BR> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=502" style="text-decoration: none" target=_blank><b>Jilariz</b></a> • <a href="http://www.interealms.com/shaman" style="text-decoration: none" target=_blank><b>Iksar Oracle</b></a> <BR> <a href="http://forums.gamerealm.com/cgi-bin/postlist.pl?Cat=75,76,77,71,72&Board=generalxegony" style="text-decoration: none" target=_blank><b>Xegony</b></a> • <a href="http://illuminati-sancti.org/" style="text-decoration: none" target=_blank><b>Illuminati Sancti</b></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessageRange?topicID=29345.topic&start=21&stop=25>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=29345.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=29345.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29345.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboar